Package graph Description

Defines and implements (using adjacency lists) graphs. Also defines, but does not implement, topologiocal sorts. Note: Topological sorts are defined as a subclass of graphs. This means that a topological sort object is a graph. It therefore doesn't need to be provided with a graph to sort. It sorts itself.

Also see the tester package, which defines tests for topological sorts. Except it doesn't, yet. You should complete the implementation of testGraph in TopologicalSortTest.
